summary:
Here is a clear and concise summary of the Security Council document:

The Security Council,
Recalling its previous resolutions and statements on the situation in Abkhazia, Georgia, 
Welcomes the report of the Secretary-General and encourages the parties to seize the opportunity of the appointment of a new Special Representative to renew their commitment to the peace process. 
The Council supports the sustained efforts of the Secretary-General and his Special Representative to promote a comprehensive political settlement, including a settlement on the political status of Abkhazia within Georgia. 
The Council calls on the parties to deepen their commitment to the UN-led peace process, expand their dialogue, and display the necessary will to achieve substantial results on key issues. 
The Council reiterates that it considers unacceptable and illegitimate the holding of self-styled elections and referendum in Abkhazia, Georgia. 
The Council calls on the parties to enhance their efforts to implement confidence-building measures and respect human rights. 
The Council welcomes the contributions of UNOMIG and the CIS peacekeeping force in stabilizing the situation and stresses the importance of their close cooperation.
Here is a clear and concise summary of the Security Council document:

The Security Council:
- Urges parties to improve observance of agreements as part of a comprehensive political settlement (para 8);
- Reaffirms the right of refugees and displaced persons to return home securely, in line with international law and the Quadripartite Agreement (para 8);
- Calls on parties to address this issue urgently and guarantee security for returnees (para 8);
- Demands strict observance of the Moscow Agreement (para 9);
- Welcomes UNOMIG's review of security arrangements for its staff (para 10);
- Extends UNOMIG's mandate until 31 July 2000, subject to review (para 11);
- Requests the Secretary-General to report regularly on the situation (para 12);
- Decides to remain actively seized of the matter (para 13).
